msDesc.head: Legislative texts for the Birgittine order: Regula Salvatoris. Petrus Olavi, Additiones ad regulam Salvatoris. Declaraciones dominorum. Liber usuum. Decisions from the General Chapter in 1487.

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil takes account of the two flyleaves. Benedicciones palmarum
supportDesc.condition: A few words illegible due to an ink-stain.

p.note: Top, in black ink by a modern hand: A 11. Regula S. Salvatoris in prima Persona. Top left corner: National Library book label with the current signum in black ink. In brown ink by a modern hand: N 93. In brown ink by a medieval hand: a reference to the contents of the volume: Hiis diebus confessor ministrabit sororibus corpus Christi followed by a list of days.
Lower right side, in dark ink by a medieval hand: R
Prayers, most likely a contemporary addition. Incipit: (R)epelle a nobis. Empty space for initials noted with letters in light brown ink and a sharper pen. Words in the right margin by the same hand.
Middle, in dark ink, annotations by a later scribe, possibly 16th or 17th century. Bottom right, in brown ink: the name Lars Hanson followed by a sentence in Swedish.

decoNote.p: : Bookmark in brown leather sewn on to page.

binding.p: Original late medieval binding. Light brown leather over wooden boards. Five raised bands on the . Two bosses of bone (traces of a third) on . Metal catches remaining on and .

origin.p: Sweden , Vadstena monastery 15th century, second half

provenance.p: The Antiquities Archive. Current signum, A 11, first established in Helin’s catalogue from the 1720s (U 91:2:2). Also mentioned in the following catalogues and inventories: U 90:2, f. 8v, no. 93; U 90:4, p. 44, no. 95.

acquisition.p: From the Antiquities Archive to the National Library in .
